Step 1: Identify the key figures.  
• From the balance sheet, the Accounts Receivable is:  
  • Beginning (2023-12-31): 0.00  
  • Ending (2024-02-01): 3,098,023.69

Step 2: Calculate the average Accounts Receivable.  
  Average AR = (Beginning AR + Ending AR) / 2  
  Average AR = (0 + 3,098,023.69) / 2 = 1,549,011.845

Step 3: From the income statement, the Main Business Revenue is: 6,836,701.10  
  (Assuming that all sales are made on credit or that the figure represents credit sales for this purpose.)

Step 4: Compute the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio using the formula:  
  Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 6,836,701.10 / 1,549,011.845  
  ≈ 4.42

Thus, the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio is approximately 4.42.
